\begin_layout Standard
In princple Fourier transform assumes the integration for in a infinite
 spectral range.
 In practice this is not possible, this limitation causes the decrease of
 the precision with which the oscilation frequencies are estimated and therefore
 decreasing the resolution to which we can observe the interace.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
In the show example, the output spectrum in measured by varying the light
 source wavelength.
 This type of operation is called swept source.
 However, it is possible to use a light source with broad spectrum, and
 distiguish the contribution of each optical frequency using a spectrometer
 principe using in the spectral radar OCT.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Section
Frequency domain OCT
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Considere o esquema da figura 3.6.
 Uma fonte de luz de baixa coerência emite uma radi- ação, cujo campo elétrico
 na saída da fonte é descrito por E (t).
 A luz é dividida no acoplador de fibra óptica, onde uma fração D da potência
 é direcionada para o espelho de referência com refletividade Rr.
 A luz então retorna ao acoplador onde (1−D), e vai para o espectrômetro.
 Analogamente, no braço da amostra, (1 − D) da luz emitida pela fonte incidem
 sobre a amostra, onde uma fração Ri que foi retro-refletida ou retro-espalhada
 na camada i retorna à fibra e uma porção D dessa se encaminha para o espectrôme
tro.
 O campo elétrico na entrada do espec- trômetro é descrito por
\begin_inset Formula \[
E\left(t\right)=\sqrt{K_{r}}E_{0}\left(t-\tau\right)+\sum_{i}\sqrt{K_{i}}E_{0}\left(t-\tau_{i}\right)\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
onde K j = R j D (1 − D) é a fração da potência da fonte que chega na entrada
 do espectrômetro e τ j é o tempo necessário para luz percorrer o caminho
 da saída da fonte até a interface j e em seguida para o espectrômetro.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The autocorrelation function of the output light electric field 
\begin_inset Formula $\Gamma\left(\tau\right)=\left\langle E\left(t\right)E^{*}\left(t-\tau\right)\right\rangle $
\end_inset


\begin_inset Formula \begin{equation}
\Gamma\left(\tau\right)=\left[K_{r}+\sum_{i}K_{i}\right]\Gamma_{0}\left(\tau\right)+\sum_{i}K_{r,i}\Gamma_{0}\left(\tau+\Delta\tau_{r,i}\right)+\sum_{i}K_{r,i}\Gamma_{0}\left(\tau-\Delta\tau_{r,i}\right)+\sum_{i\ne j}K_{i,j}\Gamma_{0}\left(\tau-\Delta\tau_{i,j}\right),\label{eq:FDautocorrelation}\end{equation}

\end_inset

where 
\begin_inset Formula $K_{a,b}=\sqrt{K_{a}K_{b}}$
\end_inset

, 
\begin_inset Formula $\Delta\tau_{a,b}=\tau_{a}-\tau_{b}=\frac{2\Delta l_{a,b}}{c}$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $\Gamma_{0}\left(\tau\right)=\left\langle E_{0}\left(t\right)E_{0}^{*}\left(t-\tau\right)\right\rangle $
\end_inset

.
 Before describing 
\begin_inset Formula $\Gamma$
\end_inset

, is worth recall that 
\begin_inset Formula $\Gamma_{0}$
\end_inset

 is complex function and therefore so is 
\begin_inset Formula $\Gamma$
\end_inset

.
 However, we are interested on the 
\begin_inset Formula $\left|\Gamma\right|$
\end_inset

.
 In section we discussed the types of 
\begin_inset Formula $\left|\Gamma_{0}\right|$
\end_inset

 and how they are related to the light source power spectral density, for
 this section it is just worth remembering that it is a peak function centered
 at argument.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The first term of the equation 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "eq:FDautocorrelation"

\end_inset

 will give raise to a peak centered at the origin, called the DC term.
 The second term are constituted of several peaks each centered at its respectiv
e delays 
\begin_inset Formula $\Delta\tau_{r,i}$
\end_inset

 and height proportional to its reflectance.
 This is the information which we are going to use in the image reconstruction.
 The third them as repeated information of the second term but inverted
 relative to the origin, called 
\emph on
mirror image
\emph default
.
 The fourht term are self interferences, due to the interference of backscattere
d light in the sample only.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Float figure
wide false
sideways false
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout
